#### DIRECTORY LAYOUT ####
##
## letsencrypt-account/<uniq_identifier>/  # directory containing an account
##     keypair
## letsencrypt-account/<uniq_identifier>/account_key.pem    the private part
## letsencrypt-account/<uniq_identifier>/account_pub.pem    the public part
## letsencrypt-account/current    symlink pointing to the currently active
##     account
##
## spool/<identifier>/  # idenifier is based on FQDN+SANs
## spool/<identifier>/domain.list  # one line with the FQDN and SANs 
## spool/<identifier>/key.pem
## spool/<identifier>/csr.pem
## spool/<identifier>/crt.pem
## spool/<identifier>/chain.pem
##     the intermediate certificates, excludeing the CA
## spool/<identifier>/ca.pem
##     the top-most ca-certificate which signed crt.pem
## spool/<identifier>/crt+chain.pem  # crt and chain concatenated
## spool/<identifier>/crt+chain+key.pem  # crt, chain and key concatenated
## spool/<identifier>/isfailed.bool
##     contains "true" or "false". Default: "false"
## spool/<identifier>/isselfsign.bool
##     contains "true" or "false". Default: "false"
## spool/<identifier>/isletsencrypt.bool
##     contains "true" or "false". Default: "false"
##
## database/items/<date_identifier>/  # the primary hold for all commited items
##     items are named with datetime of their commit, plus their identifier
##     calculated from FQDN+SANs.
## database/active/<identifier> =>  # symlink to the currently active item for
##     that identifier. the symlink must be relative.
## database/latest-by-fqdn/<fqdn> =>  # symlink to the uuid in database/active
##     the symlink must be relative.
##